"So, how did he really die?
Right?」[l][r]
"So I'm not dead." [l][r]
Chito asks, and Yuri answers. The flames flicker on their faces. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]This is Nagano. It's on top of a mountain in the Northern Alps. As soon as Mr. Ishii returned to Japan, we realized our travel plans, which had been postponed due to various circumstances. [l][r]
The members were me, my wife, Ishii-san, and of course Chito and Yuri. I'm sure people would stab me if they heard that one man and four beautiful women were camping together, but it was a tough time for us. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[bg  time="1500"  method="crossfade"  storage="camp1.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
Only Yuri and I were physically strong enough to climb the mountain. But Yuri was playing around with Chito the whole time and didn't help out at all. Well, I guess that can't be helped. [l][r]
[r] I pulled the luggage of nearly three people to the top of the mountain with all my might, and collapsed, wondering if this was heaven or hell. It was a shame that everyone except me insisted on camping in tents, even though we could have stayed in a mountain hut. [l][r]
[r]Why? [r]
Is women's camping popular? [r]
The equipment is too heavy! [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[bg  time="1000"  method="crossfade"  storage="camp.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"If I could survive, that would be the best thing, but how could I get here?
"Did you come 'this way'?" Ishii-san asks, holding a cup of coffee. [l][r]
"Hmm. I don't know," said Yuri. [l][r]
"Hey," said Ishii. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

