[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
We managed to reach the tent site before sunset, set up camp, and had dinner. [l][r]
The climate is mild, the scenery is good, and the air is nice. What's more, there are beautiful women all around. [l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

[bg  time="1000"  method="crossfade"  storage="camp2.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
The food was delicious, but my wife was busy talking with Ishii-san and Chito was busy talking with Yuri, so I was mostly alone. I'm used to it though. [l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

[bg  time="1000"  method="crossfade"  storage="camp.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]And now, sitting around the campfire, we are talking about "that world." In particular, we are talking about how Yuri survived and how he got here. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"Anyway, I found a bunch of cans. So I put them in my backpack and headed back, and when I opened the door... it was my room.
Hungarian" [l][r]

[r]Yes, the Yuri of this world was born to a Japanese-Hungarian father and a Japanese mother. [l][r]
His nationality is Japanese. He lives in both Japan and Hungary. His name is "Kubo Yuri." [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"So, I was wearing my normal T-shirt, I had run out of canned food, and I was hungry. I didn't know what to do, so I ate some snacks that were in my room and booked a flight online." [l][r]
"That kind of initiative is typical of you." [l][r]
"Oh, did you just praise me?" Yuri smiles happily. [l][r]
"Oh, I praised you so much. Good, good, good." [l][r]
"Hehehehe" [l][r]
[r]Yuri is happy like a puppy when Chito strokes his head. What a peaceful head. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
In other words, if Yuri's story is true, then Chito's hypothesis was wrong. The condition for coming to this world does not necessarily depend on "death." [l][r]
[r]Furthermore, Yuri clearly remembered when he met Chito at the location of the vehicle. This means that there seems to be at least a way to send information from here to the other side. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"So I decided I had to go to Tokyo, so I told my mom, 'I'm heading to Tokyo for a bit,' and then I biked to the airport, got on a plane, and when I got to Tokyo, Chi-chan was waiting for me!" [l][r]
[r]Yuri shouted with genuine joy, hugging Chito and rubbing his cheek against hers. [l][r]
"Stop it, don't stick to me," Chito protests, genuinely reluctant. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]……Even though his family lives in Japan and he is used to traveling back and forth, everyone thought that he was being too casual, but we ignored that. [l][r]
Because if I kept questioning everything Yuri said, the conversation would never end.

[cm]In the end, Yuri reunites with Chito and leaves his family home to stay with Chito, who lives near his university. [l][r]
[r]Even though I was attending university in Hungary, I went through various procedures and even transferred to the university in Japan where Tito was attending. [l][r]
Apparently, she is a highly promising rifle athlete on a scholarship.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]"You should try harder in your department too." [l][r]
"Oh no. Hahaha." [l][r]
"Why would you take Russian anyway?
" [l][r]
"Because Russian is kind of cool." [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[bg  time="2000"  method="crossfade"  storage="yamahosi.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
We continued this conversation for a few hours. Eventually, my wife and Yuri got sleepy and went into their tents. [l][r]
...Eh? Room assignments for the tents? My wife and Ishii-san. Chito and Yuri. I'm alone. It's like this, so what? [l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

[stopbgm  time="1000"  fadeout="true"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]The number of people decreased, and people suddenly became less talkative. So I was able to ask Chito what he thought about hearing Yuri's story. [l][r]
Ishii-san said he was also interested, so Chito, a little embarrassed, rejected his previous hypothesis and instead told me this fairy tale: [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
